Paragraph

A paragraph (from the Greek paragraphos, "to write beside" or "written beside") is a self-contained unit of a discourse in writing dealing with a particular point or idea. A paragraph consists of one or more sentences. Though not required by the syntax of any language, paragraphs are usually an expected part of formal writing, used to organize longer prose.

HTML

									
										<p>A paragraph (from the Greek paragraphos, "to write beside" or "written beside") is a self-contained unit of a discourse in writing dealing with a particular point or idea. A paragraph consists of one or more sentences. Though not required by the syntax of any language, paragraphs are usually an expected part of formal writing, used to organize longer prose.</p>

Blockquote

A block quotation (also known as a long quotation or extract) is a quotation in a written document, that is set off from the main text as a paragraph, or block of text, and typically distinguished visually using indentation and a different typeface or smaller size quotation.

HTML

									
										<blockquote>
	<p>A block quotation (also known as a long quotation or extract) is a quotation in a written document, that is set off from the main text as a paragraph, or block of text, and typically distinguished visually using indentation and a different typeface or smaller size quotation.</p>
</blockquote>

Inline Elements

This is a text link

Strong is used to indicate strong importance

This text has added emphasis

The b element is stylistically different text from normal text, without any special importance

The i element is text that is set off from the normal text

The u element is text with an unarticulated, though explicitly rendered, non-textual annotation

This text is deleted and This text is inserted

This text has a strikethrough

SuperscriptÂ®

Subscript for things like H2O

This small text is small for for fine print, etc.

Abbreviation: HTML

Keybord input: Cmd

This text is a short inline quotation

This is a citation

The dfn element indicates a definition.

The mark element indicates a highlight

This is what inline code looks like.

This is sample output from a computer program

The variable element, such as x = y

	<p><a href="#">This is a text link</a></p>

	<p><strong>Strong is used to indicate strong importance</strong></p>

	<p><em>This text has added emphasis</em></p>

	<p>The <b>b element</b> is stylistically different text from normal text, without any special importance</p>

	<p>The <i>i element</i> is text that is set off from the normal text</p>

	<p>The <u>u element</u> is text with an unarticulated, though explicitly rendered, non-textual annotation</p>

	<p><del>This text is deleted</del> and <ins>This text is inserted</ins></p>

	<p><s>This text has a strikethrough</s></p>

	<p>Superscript<sup>®</sup></p>

	<p>Subscript for things like H<sub>2</sub>O</p>

	<p><small>This small text is small for for fine print, etc.</small></p>

	<p>Abbreviation: <abbr title="HyperText Markup Language">HTML</abbr></p>

	<p>Keybord input: <kbd>Cmd</kbd></p>

	<p><q cite="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/HTML/Element/q">This text is a short inline quotation</q></p>

	<p><cite>This is a citation</cite>

	</p><p>The <dfn>dfn element</dfn> indicates a definition.</p>

	<p>The <mark>mark element</mark> indicates a highlight</p>

	<p><code>This is what inline code looks like.</code></p>

	<p><samp>This is sample output from a computer program</samp></p>

	<p>The <var>variable element</var>, such as <var>x</var> = <var>y</var></p>
</div><!--end .text-->

Unordered

  • This is a list item in an unordered list
  • An unordered list is a list in which the sequence of items is not important. Sometimes, an unordered list is a bulleted list. And this is a long list item in an unordered list that can wrap onto a new line.
  • Lists can be nested inside of each other
    • This is a nested list item
    • This is another nested list item in an unordered list
  • This is the last list item

HTML

									
										<div class="text">
	<ul>
		<li>This is a list item in an unordered list</li>
		<li>An unordered list is a list in which the sequence of items is not important. Sometimes, an unordered list is a bulleted list. And this is a long list item in an unordered list that can wrap onto a new line. </li>
		<li>
			Lists can be nested inside of each other
			<ul>
				<li>This is a nested list item</li>
				<li>This is another nested list item in an unordered list</li>
			</ul>
		</li>
		<li>This is the last list item</li>
	</ul>
</div>

Ordered

  1. This is a list item in an ordered list
  2. An ordered list is a list in which the sequence of items is important. An ordered list does not necessarily contain sequence characters.
  3. Lists can be nested inside of each other
    1. This is a nested list item
    2. This is another nested list item in an ordered list
  4. This is the last list item

HTML

									
										<div class="text">
	<ol>
		<li>This is a list item in an ordered list</li>
		<li>An ordered list is a list in which the sequence of items is important. An ordered list does not necessarily contain sequence characters.</li>
		<li>
			Lists can be nested inside of each other
			<ol>
				<li>This is a nested list item</li>
				<li>This is another nested list item in an ordered list</li>
			</ol>
		</li>
		<li>This is the last list item</li>
	</ol>
</div>

Definition

Definition List
A number of connected items or names written or printed consecutively, typically one below the other.
This is a term.
This is the definition of that term, which both live in a dl.
Here is another term.
And it gets a definition too, which is this line.
Here is term that shares a definition with the term below.
And it gets a definition too, which is this line.

HTML

									
										<dl>
	<dt>Definition List</dt>
	<dd>A number of connected items or names written or printed consecutively, typically one below the other.</dd>
    <dt>This is a term.</dt>
    <dd>This is the definition of that term, which both live in a <code>dl</code>.</dd>
    <dt>Here is another term.</dt>
    <dd>And it gets a definition too, which is this line.</dd>
    <dt>Here is term that shares a definition with the term below.</dt>
    <dd>And it gets a definition too, which is this line.</dd>
</dl>

Blockquote With Citation

A block quotation (also known as a long quotation or extract) is a quotation in a written document, that is set off from the main text as a paragraph, or block of text, and typically distinguished visually using indentation and a different typeface or smaller size quotation.

Quote Source

HTML

									
										<blockquote>
   	<p>A block quotation (also known as a long quotation or extract) is a quotation in a written document, that is set off from the main text as a paragraph, or block of text, and typically distinguished visually using indentation and a different typeface or smaller size quotation. </p>
	<cite class="citation">Quote Source</cite>
</blockquote>

    Assessment Tips

    Tips

    1. The assessment is best on a desktop computer.
    2. Set aside 40 minutes to complete.
    3. If you need to scroll within the assessment, move your cursor into the frame.
    4. Progress is auto-saved at the end of each section.
    5. Starting and stopping is OK.

    Job Detail

    Medical Support Assistant

    Location:
    Indianapolis, IN
    Company:
    Veterans Health Administration
    Minimum Experience:
    1
    Match Score:
    95%

    Apply

    This position is located in PCS/Clinical Support Service. Incumbent in this roles will be responsible for performing a variety of administrative and clerical duties and is the liaison between the nursing staff in their assigned area and customers both internal and external to the medical center.

    Specialized experience includes, but is not limited, to the following:

    • Scheduling, canceling and rescheduling patientsÂ discharge appointments.
    • Accurately and timely processing patient information, admits, discharge, appointments and transfers in computer system.
    • Arranging and coordinating in-patient procedure appointments for timeliness.
    • Maintaining office supplies.
    • Providing professional and courteous customer service.
    • Assisting with the orientation/on the job training of new staff.
    • Completing work orders and contacting appropriate staff when requested for emergency repairs or special requests.
    • Inputting and extracting data of a highly technical nature.
    • Interpreting and transcribing doctorsÂ orders.
    • Maintaining patient records, scanning, quality control

    Work Schedule: 2 shifts available

    SHIFT 1: 7:30AM Â 4:00PM, Monday through Friday working every THIRD weekend with rotating holidays. Note: Dayshift position will provide backup coverage to Decedent Affairs, duties include but not limited to releasing deceased veterans to funeral homes, updating patient deaths, providing information regarding death benefits, updating Advance Directive information in patient records.

    SHIFT 2: 3:30PM Â 12Midnight, Monday-Friday working every OTHER weekend with rotating holidays.

    Functional Statement Title/#: Medical Support Assistant, GS-679-5

    Company:
    Veterans Health Administration

    Job Engagingteaser

    Job Lead 1 of 11


    Certified Medical Assistant Medical Receptionist

    Indianapolis, IN - Veterans Health Administration


    They're looking for: Attention to Detail, Dependability, Cooperation, Integrity

    I'll be responsible for: Record patients' medical history, vital statistics, or information such as test results in medical records.

    I'll also be responsible for: Prepare treatment rooms for patient examinations, keeping the rooms neat and clean.

    I can expect to make: $14.41 hourly, $29,960 annual


    People who work here say: The people. Everyone here works as hard as they can toward a shared mission.

    They also say: Leadership is not taught or valued here - and it's needed. Managers are not empowered to make decisions for their departments, and they are not listened to.

    The cost of living is about: $2.80/gal for gas, $1400/mo for rent (900 sq. ft), and $33 to go to dinner for two

    I may be promoted to: Medical Assistant Manager

    powered by

    Better Weekdays Pattern Lab

    • Personal Motivators
    • Area Missions

    2 / 8 sections completed.

    25% Complete

    Tips

    1. The assessment is best on a desktop computer.
    2. Set aside 40 minutes to complete.
    3. If you need to scroll within the assessment, move your cursor into the frame.
    4. Progress is auto-saved at the end of each section.
    5. Starting and stopping is OK.

    What Should I Do Next?

    • Now
    • View at least 5 jobs in playlist view
    • Did you actually apply to the Medical Assistant job at Veterans Hospital?
    • Send thank-you note to Veterans Hospital for interview (why?)
    • Next Week
    • Log back in and check for new matches (why?)
    • Research salary of position (why?)

    Choose Your Better Weekday

      Leads

    Quickly view jobs without a resume.

    Best for jobs with a specific title or certification.

      Matches

    Discover new careers at established companies automatically refreshed daily.

    Requires a resume and an idea of location preference.

      Assessment

    Gain scientific insight into your leadership potential.

    Takes about 30 minutes.

      Guarantees

    Better Weekdays Pattern Lab

    Company

    Veterans Health Administration

    • Formed: 1718
    • Annual Budget: $47 billion
    • Employees: 279,792
    • Website
    • Wikipedia
    • Google Plus

    Location

    Indianapolis, IN

    • Population: 820,445
    • Avg. Monthly Cost: 2.5k
    • Humid Continental Climate
    • Events
    • Points of Interest
    • Neighborhoods

    Schedule

    40hr Week

    • 8 hr days
    • 5 days per week
    • 3 weeks time off
    • Vacation Policy
    • Sick / Personal Day Policy

    Compensation

    $29,600 Annual

    • $2,466 Monthly
    • $15.40 Hourly
    • You
    • The Job
    • What It's Like

    This position is located in PCS/Clinical Support Service. Incumbent in this roles will be responsible for performing a variety of administrative and clerical duties and is the liaison between the nursing staff in their assigned area and customers both internal and external to the medical center.

    Specialized experience includes, but is not limited, to the following:

    • Scheduling, canceling and rescheduling patientsÂ discharge appointments.
    • Accurately and timely processing patient information, admits, discharge, appointments and transfers in computer system.
    • Arranging and coordinating in-patient procedure appointments for timeliness.
    • Maintaining office supplies.
    • Providing professional and courteous customer service.
    • Assisting with the orientation/on the job training of new staff.
    • Completing work orders and contacting appropriate staff when requested for emergency repairs or special requests.
    • Inputting and extracting data of a highly technical nature.
    • Interpreting and transcribing doctorsÂ orders.
    • Maintaining patient records, scanning, quality control

    This is where the job description goes, if it exists.

    Pellentesque habitant morbi tristique senectus et netus et malesuada fames ac turpis egestas. Vestibulum tortor quam, feugiat vitae, ultricies eget, tempor sit amet, ante. Donec eu libero sit amet quam egestas semper. Aenean ultricies mi vitae est. Mauris placerat eleifend leo.

    People who work here say: The people. Everyone here works as hard as they can toward a shared mission.

    They also say: Leadership is not taught or valued here - and it's needed. Managers are not empowered to make decisions for their departments, and they are not listened to.

    Company:
    Veterans Health Administration
    Minimum Experience:
    1
    Match Score:
    95%

    Apply

    This position is located in PCS/Clinical Support Service. Incumbent in this roles will be responsible for performing a variety of administrative and clerical duties and is the liaison between the nursing staff in their assigned area and customers both internal and external to the medical center.

    Specialized experience includes, but is not limited, to the following:

    • Scheduling, canceling and rescheduling patientsÂ discharge appointments.
    • Accurately and timely processing patient information, admits, discharge, appointments and transfers in computer system.
    • Arranging and coordinating in-patient procedure appointments for timeliness.
    • Maintaining office supplies.
    • Providing professional and courteous customer service.
    • Assisting with the orientation/on the job training of new staff.
    • Completing work orders and contacting appropriate staff when requested for emergency repairs or special requests.
    • Inputting and extracting data of a highly technical nature.
    • Interpreting and transcribing doctorsÂ orders.
    • Maintaining patient records, scanning, quality control

    Work Schedule: 2 shifts available

    SHIFT 1: 7:30AM Â 4:00PM, Monday through Friday working every THIRD weekend with rotating holidays. Note: Dayshift position will provide backup coverage to Decedent Affairs, duties include but not limited to releasing deceased veterans to funeral homes, updating patient deaths, providing information regarding death benefits, updating Advance Directive information in patient records.

    SHIFT 2: 3:30PM Â 12Midnight, Monday-Friday working every OTHER weekend with rotating holidays.

    Functional Statement Title/#: Medical Support Assistant, GS-679-5

    Location:
    Indianapolis, IN
    Company:
    Veterans Health Administration
    Minimum Experience:
    1
    Match Score:
    95%

    Apply

    Job Lead 1 of 11


    Certified Medical Assistant Medical Receptionist

    Indianapolis, IN - Veterans Health Administration


    They're looking for: Attention to Detail, Dependability, Cooperation, Integrity

    I'll be responsible for: Record patients' medical history, vital statistics, or information such as test results in medical records.

    I'll also be responsible for: Prepare treatment rooms for patient examinations, keeping the rooms neat and clean.

    I can expect to make: $14.41 hourly, $29,960 annual


    People who work here say: The people. Everyone here works as hard as they can toward a shared mission.

    They also say: Leadership is not taught or valued here - and it's needed. Managers are not empowered to make decisions for their departments, and they are not listened to.

    The cost of living is about: $2.80/gal for gas, $1400/mo for rent (900 sq. ft), and $33 to go to dinner for two

    I may be promoted to: Medical Assistant Manager

    powered by


    Hint: Choosing 'No' or 'Yes' shows the next job lead.

    Better Weekdays University: Help & Resources

    Helpful Articles

    Critical Mistakes in Career Planning

    When utilizing career planning to figure out where you need to go next in life, here are five commonly made mistakes that could cause you big problems down the road.

    Source: Better Weekdays

    How to Find the Right Career Path

    Whatever you think you have planned for your career path can and will change in the future. Planning out that perfect career when you haven't even set foot in the real world can be frustrating. Instead, let yourself be guided to the right career along the way. Here are a few tips and tricks that will continuously help you stay focused in your career and keep opportunities open.

    Source: Better Weekdays

    Tips for Getting a Job After College

    Most students go to college to get a degree and to gain the skills employers want. Getting good grades is not enough to impress most employers. Students that follow the strategies listed below will be better prepared to promote themselves to employers.

    Source: iSeek Careers

    Frequently Asked Questions

    Helpful Student Engagement Tips

    What's the best way to follow-up with employers once connected?

    Follow up with thank-you notes to employers, preferably a hand written letter or postcard rather than an email.

    What is the most important step when establishing employer relationships?

    When approaching a potential partner, be sure to explain how the employer will benefit such as making valuable new connections, promoting their brand, and gaining access to potential employees.

    © 2015 Better Weekdays. All rights reserved.

    JobScript Assessment

    Self-Assessment

    Progress

    • Personal Motivators
    • Area Missions

    2 / 8 sections completed.

    25% Complete

    Tips

    1. The assessment is best on a desktop computer.
    2. Set aside 40 minutes to complete.
    3. If you need to scroll within the assessment, move your cursor into the frame.
    4. Progress is auto-saved at the end of each section.
    5. Starting and stopping is OK.

    Critical Mistakes in Career Planning

    When utilizing career planning to figure out where you need to go next in life, here are five commonly made mistakes that could cause you big problems down the road.

    Source: Better Weekdays

    How to Find the Right Career Path

    Whatever you think you have planned for your career path can and will change in the future. Planning out that perfect career when you haven't even set foot in the real world can be frustrating. Instead, let yourself be guided to the right career along the way. Here are a few tips and tricks that will continuously help you stay focused in your career and keep opportunities open.

    Source: Better Weekdays

    Tips for Getting a Job After College

    Most students go to college to get a degree and to gain the skills employers want. Getting good grades is not enough to impress most employers. Students that follow the strategies listed below will be better prepared to promote themselves to employers.

    Source: iSeek Careers

    Source: Better Weekdays

    How to Find the Right Career Path

    Whatever you think you have planned for your career path can and will change in the future. Planning out that perfect career when you haven't even set foot in the real world can be frustrating. Instead, let yourself be guided to the right career along the way. Here are a few tips and tricks that will continuously help you stay focused in your career and keep opportunities open.

    Source: Better Weekdays

    Tips for Getting a Job After College

    Most students go to college to get a degree and to gain the skills employers want. Getting good grades is not enough to impress most employers. Students that follow the strategies listed below will be better prepared to promote themselves to employers.

    Source: iSeek Careers

                                            <p class="list-group-item-text">When utilizing career planning to figure out where you need to go next in life, here are five commonly made mistakes that could cause you big problems down the road.</p>
                                            <p class="small">Source: Better Weekdays</p>
                                        </a>
                                        <a href="http://blog.betterweekdays.com/blog/students/329062/a-crooked-career-path " class="list-group-item">
                                            <h4 class="list-group-item-heading">How to Find the Right Career Path</h4>
                                            <p class="list-group-item-text">Whatever you think you have planned for your career path can and will change in the future. Planning out that perfect career when you haven't even set foot in the real world can be frustrating. Instead, let yourself be guided to the right career along the way. Here are a few tips and tricks that will continuously help you stay focused in your career and keep opportunities open.</p>
                                            <p class="small">Source: Better Weekdays</p>
                                        </a>
                                        <a href="https://www.iseek.org/careers/studentcareers.html " class="list-group-item">
                                            <h4 class="list-group-item-heading">Tips for Getting a Job After College</h4>
                                            <p class="list-group-item-text">Most students go to college to get a degree and to gain the skills employers want. Getting good grades is not enough to impress most employers. Students that follow the strategies listed below will be better prepared to promote themselves to employers.</p>
                                            <p class="small">Source: iSeek Careers</p>
                                        </a>

    Medical Support Assistant

    Company

    Veterans Health Administration

    • Formed: 1718
    • Annual Budget: $47 billion
    • Employees: 279,792
    • Website
    • Wikipedia
    • Google Plus

    Location

    Indianapolis, IN

    • Population: 820,445
    • Avg. Monthly Cost: 2.5k
    • Humid Continental Climate
    • Events
    • Points of Interest
    • Neighborhoods

    Schedule

    40hr Week

    • 8 hr days
    • 5 days per week
    • 3 weeks time off
    • Vacation Policy
    • Sick / Personal Day Policy

    Compensation

    $29,600 Annual

    • $2,466 Monthly
    • $15.40 Hourly
    • You
    • The Job
    • What It's Like

    This position is located in PCS/Clinical Support Service. Incumbent in this roles will be responsible for performing a variety of administrative and clerical duties and is the liaison between the nursing staff in their assigned area and customers both internal and external to the medical center.

    Specialized experience includes, but is not limited, to the following:

    • Scheduling, canceling and rescheduling patientsÂ discharge appointments.
    • Accurately and timely processing patient information, admits, discharge, appointments and transfers in computer system.
    • Arranging and coordinating in-patient procedure appointments for timeliness.
    • Maintaining office supplies.
    • Providing professional and courteous customer service.
    • Assisting with the orientation/on the job training of new staff.
    • Completing work orders and contacting appropriate staff when requested for emergency repairs or special requests.
    • Inputting and extracting data of a highly technical nature.
    • Interpreting and transcribing doctorsÂ orders.
    • Maintaining patient records, scanning, quality control

    This is where the job description goes, if it exists.

    Pellentesque habitant morbi tristique senectus et netus et malesuada fames ac turpis egestas. Vestibulum tortor quam, feugiat vitae, ultricies eget, tempor sit amet, ante. Donec eu libero sit amet quam egestas semper. Aenean ultricies mi vitae est. Mauris placerat eleifend leo.

    People who work here say: The people. Everyone here works as hard as they can toward a shared mission.

    They also say: Leadership is not taught or valued here - and it's needed. Managers are not empowered to make decisions for their departments, and they are not listened to.

    Medical Support Assistant

    Medical Support Assistant

    Location:
    Indianapolis, IN
    Company:
    Veterans Health Administration
    Minimum Experience:
    1
    Match Score:
    95%

    Apply

    This position is located in PCS/Clinical Support Service. Incumbent in this roles will be responsible for performing a variety of administrative and clerical duties and is the liaison between the nursing staff in their assigned area and customers both internal and external to the medical center.

    Specialized experience includes, but is not limited, to the following:

    • Scheduling, canceling and rescheduling patientsÂ discharge appointments.
    • Accurately and timely processing patient information, admits, discharge, appointments and transfers in computer system.
    • Arranging and coordinating in-patient procedure appointments for timeliness.
    • Maintaining office supplies.
    • Providing professional and courteous customer service.
    • Assisting with the orientation/on the job training of new staff.
    • Completing work orders and contacting appropriate staff when requested for emergency repairs or special requests.
    • Inputting and extracting data of a highly technical nature.
    • Interpreting and transcribing doctorsÂ orders.
    • Maintaining patient records, scanning, quality control

    Work Schedule: 2 shifts available

    SHIFT 1: 7:30AM Â 4:00PM, Monday through Friday working every THIRD weekend with rotating holidays. Note: Dayshift position will provide backup coverage to Decedent Affairs, duties include but not limited to releasing deceased veterans to funeral homes, updating patient deaths, providing information regarding death benefits, updating Advance Directive information in patient records.

    SHIFT 2: 3:30PM Â 12Midnight, Monday-Friday working every OTHER weekend with rotating holidays.

    Functional Statement Title/#: Medical Support Assistant, GS-679-5

    Location:
    Indianapolis, IN
    Company:
    Veterans Health Administration

Incumbent in this roles will be responsible for performing a variety of administrative and clerical duties and is the liaison between the nursing staff in their assigned area and customers both internal and external to the medical center.</p>
                                        <p>Specialized experience includes, but is not limited, to the following:</p>
                                            <ul>
                                                <li>Scheduling, canceling and rescheduling patientsÂ discharge appointments.</li>
                                                <li>Accurately and timely processing patient information, admits, discharge, appointments and transfers in computer system.</li>
                                                <li>Arranging and coordinating in-patient procedure appointments for timeliness.</li>
                                                <li>Maintaining office supplies.</li>
                                                <li>Providing professional and courteous customer service.</li>
                                                <li>Assisting with the orientation/on the job training of new staff.</li>
                                                <li>Completing work orders and contacting appropriate staff when requested for emergency repairs or special requests.</li>
                                                <li>Inputting and extracting data of a highly technical nature.</li>
                                                <li>Interpreting and transcribing doctorsÂ orders.</li>
                                                <li>Maintaining patient records, scanning, quality control</li>
                                            </ul>
                                        <p>Work Schedule: 2 shifts available</p>
                                        <p>SHIFT 1: 7:30AM Â 4:00PM, Monday through Friday working every THIRD weekend with rotating holidays. Note: Dayshift position will provide backup coverage to Decedent Affairs, duties include but not limited to releasing deceased veterans to funeral homes, updating patient deaths, providing information regarding death benefits, updating Advance Directive information in patient records.</p>
                                        <p>SHIFT 2: 3:30PM Â 12Midnight, Monday-Friday working every OTHER weekend with rotating holidays.</p>
                                        <p>Functional Statement Title/#: Medical Support Assistant, GS-679-5</p>

    Big lists of job titles aren't the most helpful.

    Quick summaries of each job lead helps you make a more informed decision.

    Job Lead 1 of 11


    Certified Medical Assistant Medical Receptionist

    Indianapolis, IN - Veterans Health Administration


    They're looking for: Attention to Detail, Dependability, Cooperation, Integrity

    I'll be responsible for: Record patients' medical history, vital statistics, or information such as test results in medical records.

    I'll also be responsible for: Prepare treatment rooms for patient examinations, keeping the rooms neat and clean.

    I can expect to make: $14.41 hourly, $29,960 annual


    People who work here say: The people. Everyone here works as hard as they can toward a shared mission.

    They also say: Leadership is not taught or valued here - and it's needed. Managers are not empowered to make decisions for their departments, and they are not listened to.

    The cost of living is about: $2.80/gal for gas, $1400/mo for rent (900 sq. ft), and $33 to go to dinner for two

    I may be promoted to: Medical Assistant Manager

    powered by
